      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model and contact formulation appropriate for quasi-static compression-bending of metallic spinal implant construct.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity adopted for Ti-6Al-4V screw and PEEK rod. Augmented Lagrangian contact at screw-rod interface captures load transfer fidelity. Literature precedent supports this formulation for F1717 loading regime."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
