      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample population representative of production geometry and material lot, with sufficient replicates for statistical comparison.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-released components across two independent laboratories. Sample size supports two-sided 90% confidence interval on mean stiffness. Lot traceability confirmed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of physiological loading scenarios relevant to the intended clinical application.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted at a single compression-bending load ratio per ASTM F1717 protocol. Additional load ratios (e.g. torsion-bending) not included in this validation activity, resulting in achieved level below required. Risk accepted given conservative load case selection."
